\subsection{Usage}

Using a paperclip to attach a stack of papers is a simple task:

\begin{enumerate}
\item Collect the papers in an orderly stack.
\item Gently pinch the stack of papers together near the area where the paperclip is to be applied. This is usually the top-left corner of portrait-oriented A4 sized paper. 
\item Hold the paper clip opposite the side with the two clip-ends.
\item Maintaining a pinch on the papers, lay the tip of the paperclip's long clip-end flush with the back of the stack of papers.
\item Keeping the papers flush with the long clip-end, gently separate the long
clip-end away from the short clip-end, exposing a small gap between which the
two papers can be inserted.  
\end{enumerate}

